<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  acu bootstrap customization package template (SPEC T2 + T11 + T12).

  package_zip() (bootstrap.py) parses this template and injects a
  <Graph ClassName="AcuBootstrapPlugin" FileType="NewFile" Source="..."/>
  item carrying bootstrap_plugin.cs - the CustomizationPlugin that enables
  features on publish (CS100000 is un-writable through the contract API;
  T3 verdict). Item shape verified vs 26.101.0225: Customization.CstCodeFile
  Tag=Graph, source rides in the Source ATTRIBUTE (XML-escaped), not CDATA.

  Root element shape verified vs the training packages shipped on the live
  box (HelpAndTraining/T*/PhoneRepairShop.zip, same 26.101.0225 build):
  project.xml's root is <Customization level description product-version>;
  the project NAME comes from the import call, not the XML.

  The <EntityEndpoint> item (T12, verified vs 26.101.0225 by import
  round-trip 2026-07-08): the <Endpoint> child is the XmlSerializer form of
  PX.Api.ContractBased.Common.Model.Endpoint - namespace
  http://www.acumatica.com/entity/maintenance/5.31 (the earlier
  entity/data-model guess is what the importer rejected as "Unknown root
  node"), systemContractVersion 4 (SystemContracts.V4, the build's only
  IsCurrent implementation). No .endpoint file is involved - the
  PX.Api.ContractBased.Common.dll "*.endpoint" globs belong to the
  source-control folder layout, not the package zip. The server's own
  getProject re-serialization carries no attributes on <EntityEndpoint>;
  identity comes from the child's name/version.

  Entity payload (screen->graph->view->DAC chain read off the live box):
  - Company    CS101500 -> OrganizationMaint, PrimaryView BAccount
                (DAC PX.Objects.CS.DAC.OrganizationBAccount); the old
                draft's Organization view / OrganizationCD do not exist on
                this build. Mappings follow the screen's OWN bindings
                (CS101500.aspx read off the live box, T13) - a DAC prop
                existing on the primary view is not enough, writes only
                land through the view the screen edits:
                - AcctCD/AcctName -> BAccount (primary view);
                - OrganizationType/BaseCuryID -> OrganizationView
                  (PX.Objects.GL.DAC.Organization; the BAccount projections
                  of these echo the PUT but insert an empty GL row - 422
                  "BaseCuryID cannot be empty");
                - CountryID -> AddressDummy (PX.Objects.CR.Address, the
                  Main Address binding; the graph inserts the Address row
                  on first save and its CountryID is required - 422).
  - CreditTerms CS206500 -> TermsMaint, PrimaryView TermsDef
                (DAC PX.Objects.CS.Terms); DayDue00 is Nullable<Int16>
                -> ShortValue, DiscPercent Nullable<Decimal> -> DecimalValue.
  - Currency   CM202000 -> CurrencyMaint, PrimaryView CuryListRecords
                (DAC PX.Objects.CM.CurrencyList) - the financial-currency
                screen the Default endpoint lacks (B8: Default Currency =
                CM201000 list only, UseForAccounting creates no CM.Currency
                row, EUR-denominated accounts 422). Screen bindings read
                off CM202000.aspx (T29):
                - CuryID/Description/CurySymbol/DecimalPlaces/IsActive/
                  IsFinancial -> CuryListRecords (IsFinancial is what makes
                  the currency financial; DecimalPlaces Nullable<Int16> ->
                  ShortValue, booleans -> BooleanValue);
                - the GL Accounts tab -> CuryRecords (DAC PX.Objects.CM.
                  Currency, Current-keyed on CurrencyList.curyID); every
                  gain/loss AcctID/SubID pair carries PXDefault(
                  PersistingCheck.Null) with no setup default, so the
                  endpoint exposes all ten pairs - BUT the four
                  Translation* pairs are feature-gated (live-verified
                  T29): the API accepts them on PUT yet omits them from
                  reads while financial-statement translation is off, so
                  seed YAML must supply the other eight pairs and must
                  NOT claim Translation* (claiming them = permanent
                  phantom drift - every diff reports them missing, every
                  seed run re-PUTs). Segment masks take the CD string
                  -> StringValue (Default-endpoint idiom).
  - GLPreferences GL102000 -> GLSetupMaint, PrimaryView GLSetupRecord
                (DAC PX.Objects.GL.GLSetup) - the GL setup singleton every
                Finance screen requires (PXSetupNotEnteredException until a
                row exists). Screen ID verified vs the live site map (T34):
                General Ledger Preferences = GL102000 on this build;
                GL105000 (the training-data ID) has no site-map row at all.
                Bindings read off GL102000.aspx: YtdNetIncAccountID and
                RetEarnAccountID sit directly on the primary GLSetupRecord
                view as Account segment masks (CD string -> StringValue),
                both PXDefault with no default value - required at persist,
                so the seed data must supply real accounts. Every other
                GLSetup field carries a PXDefault value (BATCH numbering
                etc.), which settles the entity's field set: the two
                accounts only. This build's GLSetup has no RetEarnSubID or
                YtdNetIncSubID companions.
  - LedgerCompany GL201500 -> GeneralLedgerMaint, PrimaryView LedgerRecords
                (DAC PX.Objects.GL.Ledger) - the org-ledger link the
                Default endpoint cannot write (B12: the Ledger.Companies
                detail PUT answers 200 and echoes the row, but the link
                table stays empty). The screen-writable surface is the
                Companies tab view OrganizationLedgerLinkWithOrganizationSelect,
                declared on the nested OrganizationLedgerLinkMaint extension
                (DAC PX.Objects.GL.DAC.OrganizationLedgerLink; contract
                mappings resolve view names across extensions): LedgerCD
                locates the ledger on the primary view, OrganizationID
                inserts the link row. T36 bindings: graph/view names read
                off GL201500.aspx + static member reflection - the
                constructor-running reflection probe stack-overflows on the
                ledger graphs.
  - FinancialYearSettings GL101000 -> FiscalYearSetupMaint, PrimaryView
                FiscalYearSetup (DAC PX.Objects.GL.FinYearSetup) - the
                FinYearSetup singleton master-calendar generation requires
                (missing on a fresh tenant, so GL201000 500s before it
                starts - T36). BegFinYear DateTime -> DateTimeValue,
                FinPeriods Nullable<Int16> -> ShortValue. The GeneratePeriods
                action (mappedTo AutoFill, PXAction on this graph) fills
                the period-detail grid the screen's validation demands - a
                bare field PUT fails "configure all the Financial Periods"
                (T36).
  - MasterCalendar GL201000 -> MasterFinPeriodMaint, PrimaryView FiscalYear
                (DAC PX.Objects.GL.FinPeriods.MasterFinYear) - master
                financial calendar. FinancialYear -> the view's Year key.
                The GenerateCalendar action (mappedTo GenerateYears) and its
                FromYear/ToYear dialog view GenerateParams live on the
                GenerateCalendarExtensionBase graph extension.
  - CompanyCalendar GL201100 -> OrganizationFinPeriodMaint, PrimaryView
                OrgFinYear (DAC PX.Objects.GL.FinPeriods.OrganizationFinYear)
                - the company-period surface (FinancialYear + OrganizationID),
                the done_when probe target for calendar generation: master
                rows alone do not post, the per-company FinPeriod rows do
                (B12's "07-2026 does not exist for the LAB5 company"). The
                OpenPeriods action (mappedTo Open, on the
                FinPeriodStatusActionsGraphBaseExtension) ships as T37 probe
                material only - the Open flow redirects to the GL503000
                processing screen, unfollowable over contract (B13).
  Contract field names = DAC property names verbatim (no rename layer).
  Features (CS100000) stays OUT of the endpoint - writes through any
  contract endpoint do not persist (T3 verdict); the plugin owns features.
-->
<Customization level="" description="acu bootstrap: CustomizationPlugin enables features on publish; Bootstrap endpoint exposes company + credit terms + financial currency + GL preferences + ledger-company link + financial year + calendars" product-version="26.101">
  <EntityEndpoint>
    <Endpoint xmlns="http://www.acumatica.com/entity/maintenance/5.31" name="Bootstrap" version="1.3.0" systemContractVersion="4">
      <TopLevelEntity name="Company" screen="CS101500">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="AcctCD" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="AcctName" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="OrganizationType" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="BaseCuryID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="CountryID" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="AcctCD">
            <To object="BAccount" field="AcctCD" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="AcctName">
            <To object="BAccount" field="AcctName" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="OrganizationType">
            <To object="OrganizationView" field="OrganizationType" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="BaseCuryID">
            <To object="OrganizationView" field="BaseCuryID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="CountryID">
            <To object="AddressDummy" field="CountryID" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="CreditTerms" screen="CS206500">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="TermsID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="Descr" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="VisibleTo" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="DueType" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="DayDue00" type="ShortValue" />
          <Field name="DiscType" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="DiscPercent" type="DecimalValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="TermsID">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="TermsID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="Descr">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="Descr" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="VisibleTo">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="VisibleTo" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="DueType">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="DueType" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="DayDue00">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="DayDue00" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="DiscType">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="DiscType" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="DiscPercent">
            <To object="TermsDef" field="DiscPercent" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="Currency" screen="CM202000">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="CuryID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="Description" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="CurySymbol" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="DecimalPlaces" type="ShortValue" />
          <Field name="IsActive" type="BooleanValue" />
          <Field name="IsFinancial" type="BooleanValue" />
          <Field name="RealGainAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RealGainSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RealLossAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RealLossSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RevalGainAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RevalGainSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RevalLossAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RevalLossSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="TranslationGainAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="TranslationGainSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="TranslationLossAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="TranslationLossSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="UnrealizedGainAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="UnrealizedGainSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="UnrealizedLossAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="UnrealizedLossSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RoundingGainAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RoundingGainSubID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RoundingLossAcctID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RoundingLossSubID" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="CuryID">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="CuryID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="Description">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="Description" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="CurySymbol">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="CurySymbol" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="DecimalPlaces">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="DecimalPlaces" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="IsActive">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="IsActive" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="IsFinancial">
            <To object="CuryListRecords" field="IsFinancial" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RealGainAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RealGainAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RealGainSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RealGainSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RealLossAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RealLossAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RealLossSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RealLossSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RevalGainAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RevalGainAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RevalGainSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RevalGainSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RevalLossAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RevalLossAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RevalLossSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RevalLossSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="TranslationGainAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="TranslationGainAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="TranslationGainSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="TranslationGainSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="TranslationLossAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="TranslationLossAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="TranslationLossSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="TranslationLossSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="UnrealizedGainAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="UnrealizedGainAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="UnrealizedGainSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="UnrealizedGainSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="UnrealizedLossAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="UnrealizedLossAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="UnrealizedLossSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="UnrealizedLossSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RoundingGainAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RoundingGainAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RoundingGainSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RoundingGainSubID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RoundingLossAcctID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RoundingLossAcctID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RoundingLossSubID">
            <To object="CuryRecords" field="RoundingLossSubID" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="LedgerCompany" screen="GL201500">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="LedgerCD" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="OrganizationID" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="LedgerCD">
            <To object="LedgerRecords" field="LedgerCD" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="OrganizationID">
            <To object="OrganizationLedgerLinkWithOrganizationSelect" field="OrganizationID" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="FinancialYearSettings" screen="GL101000">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="BegFinYear" type="DateTimeValue" />
          <Field name="FinPeriods" type="ShortValue" />
          <Field name="PeriodType" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="BegFinYear">
            <To object="FiscalYearSetup" field="BegFinYear" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="FinPeriods">
            <To object="FiscalYearSetup" field="FinPeriods" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="PeriodType">
            <To object="FiscalYearSetup" field="PeriodType" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
        <Actions>
          <Action name="GeneratePeriods" mappedTo="AutoFill" isDefault="false" />
        </Actions>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="MasterCalendar" screen="GL201000">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="FinancialYear" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="FinancialYear">
            <To object="FiscalYear" field="Year" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
        <Actions>
          <Action name="GenerateCalendar" mappedTo="GenerateYears" isDefault="false">
            <Fields>
              <Field name="FromYear" type="StringValue" />
              <Field name="ToYear" type="StringValue" />
            </Fields>
            <Mappings>
              <Mapping field="FromYear">
                <To object="GenerateParams" field="FromYear" />
              </Mapping>
              <Mapping field="ToYear">
                <To object="GenerateParams" field="ToYear" />
              </Mapping>
            </Mappings>
          </Action>
        </Actions>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="CompanyCalendar" screen="GL201100">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="FinancialYear" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="OrganizationID" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="FinancialYear">
            <To object="OrgFinYear" field="Year" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="OrganizationID">
            <To object="OrgFinYear" field="OrganizationID" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
        <Actions>
          <Action name="OpenPeriods" mappedTo="Open" isDefault="false" />
        </Actions>
      </TopLevelEntity>
      <TopLevelEntity name="GLPreferences" screen="GL102000">
        <Fields>
          <Field name="YtdNetIncAccountID" type="StringValue" />
          <Field name="RetEarnAccountID" type="StringValue" />
        </Fields>
        <Mappings>
          <Mapping field="YtdNetIncAccountID">
            <To object="GLSetupRecord" field="YtdNetIncAccountID" />
          </Mapping>
          <Mapping field="RetEarnAccountID">
            <To object="GLSetupRecord" field="RetEarnAccountID" />
          </Mapping>
        </Mappings>
      </TopLevelEntity>
    </Endpoint>
  </EntityEndpoint>
</Customization>
